response: #5, #11, #17, #23, #24  As a university student with an interest in sustainable transportation and accessible city amenities, I prioritize projects that promote cycling, pedestrian safety, and low-carbon mobility. Safe bike paths are important for daily commutes (#5), free bike workshops encourage self-sufficiency and cycling (#11), designated bike lanes help in safe travel and reduce conflict with vehicles (#17), and initiatives like a bicycle moving trailer support eco-friendly moving options (#23). Finally, I support creating car-free zones (#24) as they can improve urban livability and reduce pollution.

response: #5, #6, #11, #17, #23 As a university student in Zurich who likely relies on safe and sustainable transportation, I'd prioritize projects that improve and promote cycling and public transit. response: #5,#7,#11,#17,#23  As a university student in Zurich interested in sustainable transportation and environmental initiatives, I'd prioritize projects that benefit both of these areas. Safe bike paths (#5) and free bike-fixing workshops (#11) can encourage cycling among my fellow students. A car-free zone in Langstrasse (#17) aligns with my preference for pedestrian-friendly urban areas. Car-free Sundays (#10) would be a nice initiative, but I favor regular and tangible changes over occasional events. Bird houses (#19) and planting workshops (#1) are valuable for biodiversity, but I believe that the projects I've chosen will have a more immediate impact on daily life and local infrastructure.
